  <title class="- topic/title ">Offer Hosting</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">You can host offers on your server, on
	 Target's server, or on a third party server. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
    <p class="- topic/p ">Use the method best suited to your architecture. In
		the 
		<xref href="c_Offers.xml#concept_40CA4EEBF72C430395ADB96C3A3D7DF4" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref ">offers</xref>,
		insert a relative or absolute URL to refer to the content, as best suited to
		your file structure. You must load your offers before creating a campaign. 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">See 
		<xref href="c_About_Dynamic_Content.xml#concept_657016A0E6174C22B89036E9C8A0170F" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref ">About Dynamic
		  Content</xref> for help choosing the best place to host your dynamic content. 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">See 
		<xref href="c_Managing_Hosts.xml#concept_BDF83A0B965A4CD486B16DAEA2F87BA7" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref "><?xm-replace_text Hosts?></xref>
		for details about managing your hosts. 
	 </p>
  </conbody>
